   LIONEL Corp. (New York) -- Moody's Investors Service Inc.
said it downgraded to Caa from single-B-2 its rating on this
specialty toy maker's 8% convertible subordinated debentures,
due 2007, and 12.375% subordinated notes, due 1996. The
rating concern's move affects about $64 million of Lionel
debt still outstanding from the two issues, which initially
totaled $70 million. Moody's didn't elaborate on the rating
change.
