   Business Brief -- Iomega Corp.:
   Quarterly Profit Grew 80%;
   Output Performance Cited
</HL>
<DATE>
07/16/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B6B
</SO>
<CO>
   IOMG
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
</IN>
<LP>
   Iomega Corp., citing better manufacturing performance,
said its second-quarter earnings were up 80% on a slight
increase in sales.
   Iomega, which makes data-storage equipment for computers,
said its net income was $3 million, or 18 cents a share, up
from $1.7 million, or 10 cents a share, in the year-ago
period. Sales grew 4.6% to $27.2 million from $26 million.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The Roy, Utah, company attributed the net income rise to
increased gross margins stemming from better manufacturing
performance and product-cost reductions. Iomega said its
gross margins were 48% in the quarter, compared with 41% in
the year-ago period. The company said its improved margins
allowed it to invest more in sales and marketing and in
research and development in the period.
