<HL>
   Spanish Car Sales Slump 21%
</HL>
<DATE>
07/16/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   EUROP
</CO>
<IN>
AUTOMOBILES (AUT)
</IN>
<LP>
   MADRID -- Spanish car sales plummeted 21% in June to
91,818 cars from 115,618 cars a year earlier, the Spanish
Association of Car Makers said.
   The result brought sales in the year's first six months to
542,184 cars, down 8.7% from 593,801 cars a year earlier.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The drop in June sales exceeded even the most pessimistic
projections, which anticipated a 16% decline.
   The association said Spain's tight credit restrictions,
coupled with a value-added tax of 33%, has hit auto sales
hard.
</TEXT>
