<LP>
   CANTON, Ohio -- Timken Co. said it filed with the
Securities and Exchange Commission for a proposed public
offering of as much as $250 million in debt securities.
   The industrial manufacturer said it expects to issue from
time to time these debt securities as medium-term notes, with
terms to be determined at the time of each sale.
</LP>
